Q4: Backend Server
Problem Description:
Create a simple backend server using Go that handles CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for a user management system. The users are stored in an SQLite database.

Solution Explanation:
Use Goâ€™s net/http package to handle HTTP requests.
Set up SQLite database for storing users.
Define CRUD routes:
GET /users: Fetch all users.
GET /users/{id}: Fetch a specific user by ID.
POST /users: Create a new user.
PUT /users/{id}: Update an existing user.
DELETE /users/{id}: Delete a user.
